        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-26 18:33:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, approved\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nI'm OK if this patch lands as-is, but it could also be improved a bit.\n\nI wouldn't be surprised if this couldn't also cause a crash, since this errant memcpy() is corrupting the fld_cache_entry fce_lru and fce_list list pointers.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "c31f0fb7f0ce8472c1e5057c640372acfe500d30",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-26 18:41:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> I wouldn't be surprised if this couldn't also cause a crash, since this errant memcpy() is corrupting the fld_cache_entry fce_lru and fce_list list pointers.\n\nI agree with you comment inline about preferring assignment to memcpy() but the part above leaves me puzzled.  Could you take a second look?",
